<abstract>
<para>
&kappname; is an count-and-capture like board game. It's in the mancala family invented by William Julius Champion Jr in 1940. This game heavily favors the starting player, who will always win the three-seed to five-seed versions with perfect play. This game is sometimes also called "Kalahari", "Kalah", "Kalaha" or "Mancala".
</para>
</abstract>

