<chapter id="introduction"><title>Introduction</title>
<note><title>Gametype:</title><para>Board</para></note>
<note><title>Number of possible players:</title><para>One, Two</para></note>

<para>
&kappname; is a board game in the mancala family. This is Kalah type of Mancala game is the most popular and commercially available variant of mancala in the West.
</para>

<para>
The game requires a Kalah board and 48 seeds or counters. The board has six small pits, called houses, on each side; and a big pit, called a Kalah, store or treasury, at each end. The game is started with four seeds in each house.
</para>

</chapter>

